Description: NDAA works both legislatively and through publications and training programs to provide a voice and information for prosecutors.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: NDAA is the largest and oldest professional organization representing criminal prosecutors in the world.  NDAA aims at representing the views of prosecutors to influence federal and national policies and programs that impact law enforcement and prosecution. The primary purpose of the NDAA is to foster and maintain the honor and integrity of the prosecuting attorneys of all titles in both large and small jurisdictions of the United States.  It works to improve and facilitate the administration of justice, to promote the study and research of the law, the diffusion of knowledge and the continuing education of prosecuting attorneys, lawyers, law enforcement personnel, and other members of the interested public through various activities such as arranging seminars and fostering periodic conventions or meetings for the discussion and solution of legal problems affecting the public interest in the administration of justice.  It causes the publishing and to distribution of addresses, reports, treatises, other literary works on legal subjects or other related subjects; and operates the training and education division of the corporation, which has been sponsored by the corporation since 1969. The NDAA is headquartered in Alexandria, Virginia, along with the training, research and development division. The training and education division and the National Advocacy Center are located in Columbia, South Carolina.

Full Description: Via Novus Capital provides managing, operating, and/or facilitating insurance and healthcare-specific claim receivable portfolios for large and small healthcare venues. It offers balance sheet liquidity at the right price via non-recourse purchase and financing of healthcare accounts receivables, insurance and government receivables, and third party claims against automobile and worker compensation insurance companies. The company provides its services for insurance and institutional healthcare receivable asset classes, such as uncollected and unidentified claims from health insurance carriers; missed opportunities to obtain reimbursement from Medicare or Medicaid; claims against other responsible third parties via liens against damage awards in civil proceedings; claims against non-health insurance carriers for no-fault, medical payment, or workers’ compensation coverage; and unbilled insurance claims and claims denied by health insurance, and property and casualty carriers. It also offers its services for consumer healthcare receivable asset classes, including installment financial obligations resulting from elective procedures financed directly from the provider; patient self-pay financial obligations, including uncollected co-pay and deductible amounts; and uncollected financial obligations from the uninsured.
